# Database — {{ORM}} + {{DB_TYPE}}

## ORM CONVENTIONS
- Schema/models in: `{{SCHEMA_DIR}}/`
- Client instance in: `{{DB_CLIENT_PATH}}` — import from there, NEVER instantiate elsewhere
- DO: `{{QUERY_PATTERN}}`
<!-- QUERY_PATTERN example for Prisma: "Use prisma.user.findUnique() over raw SQL unless performance requires it" -->

## MIGRATIONS
- Generate: `{{CMD_MIGRATE_GENERATE}}`
- Apply (dev): `{{CMD_MIGRATE_DEV}}`
- Apply (prod): `{{CMD_MIGRATE_PROD}}`
- NEVER edit migration files after applying — create a new migration instead

## QUERY RULES
- DO: Select only needed fields — NEVER `SELECT *` / `findMany()` without `select:`
- DO: Use transactions for multi-step writes
- DO NOT: Run queries in loops — use batch operations (`createMany`, `updateMany`)
- DO NOT: Expose raw DB errors to API responses

## SEEDING
- Seed command: `{{CMD_SEED}}`
- Seed files: `{{SEED_DIR}}/`

## CONNECTIONS
- Connection string from env: `{{DB_URL_ENV_VAR}}`
- Connection pooling: {{POOL_CONFIG}}
<!-- POOL_CONFIG example: "PgBouncer in transaction mode — max 10 connections per instance" -->

## AFTER SCHEMA CHANGES
Run: `{{CMD_MIGRATE_DEV}}` → `{{CMD_GENERATE_TYPES}}` → `{{CMD_TYPECHECK}}`
